  "description" : "Before being heated, the temperature of the water in a tank is 18°C. <br> Most people take a shower at 38°C (a little bit above body temperature).<br><br> According to thermodynamic, heating 1L of water from 18 to 38°C consume 0.0232 kWh. <br><br><b>Formula:</b> Energy [kWh] = (mass of water [g] x specific heat capacity [J/g°C] x delta T [°C]) / conversion coefficient [J/kWh] <br><b>Details:</b> (1 000 x 4.18 x (38 - 18)) / 3 600 000 = 0.0232",
